[The news report above says that there has been an increase in cases of chlamydia infection and gonorrhea in Humboldt County, as well as other counties that constitute the "North Coast" in the US state of California. The report says that the increase may have been facilitated by use of apps that allow anonymous sexual hook-ups [through the internet], but does characterize the cases further. ProMED-mail would appreciate more information on this outbreak from knowledgeable sources.

Humboldt County, with a population was 134 623 in 2010, is located in the US state of California along the Pacific coast, 200 miles (322 km) north of the city of San Francisco (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humboldt_County,_California). The North Coast of California is the region in Northern California that lies on the Pacific coast between San Francisco Bay and the US state of Oregon border. It commonly includes Humboldt, Mendocino, and Del Norte counties and sometimes includes 2 counties from the San Francisco Bay area, Marin and Sonoma (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Coast_(California)). A map of California counties is available at http://www.socalequest.com/map.htm.
- Mod.ML

